etadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1110:      \"self\": \"https://api.github.com/repos/apache/parquet-java/contents/parquet-jackson/src/main/resources?ref=apache-parquet-1.12.2\",\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1112:      \"html\": \"https://github.com/apache/parquet-java/tree/apache-parquet-1.12.2/parquet-jackson/src/main/resources\"\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1153:parquet-jackson module will create a new jar artifact containing all Jackson classes, relocated under *parquet.com.fasterxml.jackson.core* package. The shade plugin will transform *pom.xml* too to remove any reference to Jackson dependency.\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1155:Other Parquet modules which requires Jackson are configured to depend on parquet-jackson module and still perform shading. The difference is that all Jackson classes are excluded from inclusion, but references from Parquet to Jackson classes are still relocated. The shade plugin will also remove any reference to Jackson dependency but will preserve the parquet-jackson dependency which contains the relocated classes.\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact_metadata.log:1159:Because of the way Maven handles multi-modules project. Let's assume that parquet-foo module uses Jackson. When executing *mvn package*, parquet-jackson module will be built first and artifact will be packaged, and a new pom.xml without Jackson dependency is created and used by parquet-foo module. Since Jackson dependencies have been removed by the shade plugin, compilation of parquet-foo will fail.\nhuman-intervention-logs/org.apache.parquet:parquet-jackson:1.12.2/discover-artifact-metadata/discover_artifact